prompt_for_description_check:
You are a log description validator. Validate the following task description against these rules:

1. It should be clear, descriptive, and holds a little bit of the context.
2. It should include links or references related to the task.

Task Description: "{description}"

Return your response strictly in JSON with:
- "status": should be "pass" or "fail"
- "reason": required only if status is "fail" (mention the reason). If status is "pass", reason will be "Complete description."
Remember reason should not be longer than 30 words.

Example output:

Input: {{
  "DayDetailID": "123",
  "TaskLabel": "Project Management",
  "CompetencyRoles": "Product Manager",
  "DecimalHours": 5.5,
  "TaskDescription": "Attended daily standup and worked on bug fix."
}}
Output: {{
  "status": "fail",
  "reason": "Description is too short and lacks context."
}}

OR

Input: {{
  "DayDetailID": "123",
  "TaskLabel": "coding",
  "CompetencyRoles": "Software Engineer",
  "DecimalHours": 5.5,
  "TaskDescription": "Verified on iOS 1.2.7 (210)\nhttps://travly.atlassian.net/browse/TRAV-106 Moved to In Dev\nhttps://travly.atlassian.net/browse/TRAV-127 QA Failed\nhttps://travly.atlassian.net/browse/TRAV-121\nhttps://travly.atlassian.net/browse/TRAV-103\nhttps://travly.atlassian.net/browse/TRAV-119\nhttps://travly.atlassian.net/browse/TRAV-126\nhttps://travly.atlassian.net/browse/TRAV-106 Second testing cycle after fixes"
}}
Output: {{
  "status": "pass",
  "reason": "Complete description."
}}
